Reasoning: The paper deals with metrics and weights over finite fields, which are common topics in information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The classification of sets of equivalent weights and the characterization of linear isometries suggest a focus on discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and coding theory (cs.CC). Finally, the use of decision criteria and the representation of all possible criteria suggest a connection to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.SI).
